  <compounddef id="DATA" kind="page">
    <compoundname>DATA</compoundname>
    <title>DATA Keyword</title>
    <briefdescription>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para><programlisting filename=".basic"><codeline><highlight class="normal">DATA<sp/>value,<sp/>value,<sp/>value</highlight></codeline>
</programlisting></para>
<para>Defines a sequence of constant values embedded in the program.</para>
<para>Values may be:</para>
<para><itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>integers</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>real numbers</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>strings (in double quotes)</para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
<para>Values are stored at program load time and are not re-parsed during execution.</para>
<para>Multiple <computeroutput>DATA</computeroutput> statements are concatenated into a single continuous data stream.</para>
<para><hruler/>
</para>
<sect1 id="DATA_1example-11_1s1"><sect2 id="DATA_1example-11_1s2"><sect3 id="DATA_1example-11_1s3"><sect4 id="DATA_1example-11_1s4"><sect5 id="DATA_1example-11">
<title>Example</title><para><programlisting filename=".basic"><codeline><highlight class="normal">DATA<sp/>10,<sp/>20</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">DATA<sp/>1.5</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">DATA<sp/>&quot;ok&quot;</highlight></codeline>
</programlisting></para>
<para><hruler/>
</para>
</sect5></sect4></sect3></sect2></sect1>
<sect1 id="DATA_1behaviour-3_1s1"><sect2 id="DATA_1behaviour-3_1s2"><sect3 id="DATA_1behaviour-3_1s3"><sect4 id="DATA_1behaviour-3_1s4"><sect5 id="DATA_1behaviour-3">
<title>Behaviour</title><para><itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>Values are stored in the order they appear across all <computeroutput>DATA</computeroutput> statements.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>The data stream is shared across the entire program.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para><computeroutput>DATA</computeroutput> statements are not executed; they are processed during program load.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Values are consumed sequentially by data-reading functions.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Attempting to read beyond the available data results in a runtime error.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Values are strongly typed; no implicit conversion occurs during reading.</para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
<para><hruler/>
</para>
</sect5></sect4></sect3></sect2></sect1>
